    "inscribed":"Printed along bottom: Learning is Wealth. / Wilson, Charley, Rebecca & Rosa / Slaves from New Orleans.\r\n\r\nPrinted on verso: No. 6. / Entered according to act of Congress, in the year 1864, by S. TACKABERRY, in the Clerk's Office of the U.S. for the Southern District of New-York. / The nett proceeds from the sale of these Photographs will be devoted to the education of colored people in the department of the Gulf, now under the command of Maj. Gen. Banks. / CHAS. PAXSON, PHOTOGRAPHER, N.Y. / N. B.–All orders must be addressed to H. N. BENT, No. 1 Mercer Street, N. Y.",
